# What an RDD actually is

## The original Spark abstraction

- **RDD** = Resilient Distributed Dataset — every DataFrame compiles down to RDD ops
- Understanding it explains **why** Spark is lazy, fault-tolerant, and partition-parallel

## Read the three letters

- **Resilient** — lost partitions **recomputed from lineage**, not a replica
- **Distributed** — partitioned across executor memory on many machines
- **Dataset** — a collection of records (any object) — **no schema, no columns**

## Four properties

- **Immutable** · **Lazy** · **Schema-free** · **Typed** at runtime
